node.title: Victoria records 1,622 new COVID-19 cases and nine deaths
node.alt: A couple walking in Melbourne's CBD.
node.description: There are now 12,252 active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 617 people have died during the current outbreak.
node.content:
["Victoria has recorded 1,622\u00a0new COVID-19 cases and nine\u00a0deaths.", "It's the state's highest daily case count since late October.", "There are now 12,252\u00a0active cases of the virus in Victoria, and 617\u00a0people have died during the current outbreak.", "There are 384\u00a0people in hospital with the virus, of whom 87\u00a0are in intensive care and 49\u00a0are on a ventilator.", "The health department said a further 35\u00a0people were in ICU but their infections were no longer considered active.", "The seven-day average for hospitalisations has risen for the past nine days, from 296 on December 7 to 340 today.", "The new cases were detected from 80,841\u00a0test results received yesterday.", "There were 10,816\u00a0doses of vaccine administered at state-run sites yesterday, as well as more vaccinations at GP clinics and other venues.", "More to come.", "", "
Why we hear about some COVID-19 variants more than others
"]
